{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:job.35",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 35,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 35",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 35 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.35.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:1",
      "text": "Elihu spake moreover, and said,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.35.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:2",
      "text": "Thinkest thou this to be right, that thou saidst, My righteousness is more than God’s?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.35.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:3",
      "text": "For thou saidst, What advantage will it be unto thee? and, What profit shall I have, if I be cleansed from my sin?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.35.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:4",
      "text": "I will answer thee, and thy companions with thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.35.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:5",
      "text": "Look unto the heavens, and see; and behold the clouds which are higher than thou.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.35.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:6",
      "text": "If thou sinnest, what doest thou against him? or if thy transgressions be multiplied, what doest thou unto him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.35.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:7",
      "text": "If thou be righteous, what givest thou him? or what receiveth he of thine hand?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.35.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:8",
      "text": "Thy wickedness may hurt a man as thou art; and thy righteousness may profit the son of man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.35.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:9",
      "text": "By reason of the multitude of oppressions they make the oppressed to cry: they cry out by reason of the arm of the mighty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.35.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:10",
      "text": "But none saith, Where is God my maker, who giveth songs in the night;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.35.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:11",
      "text": "Who teacheth us more than the beasts of the earth, and maketh us wiser than the fowls of heaven?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.35.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:12",
      "text": "There they cry, but none giveth answer, because of the pride of evil men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.35.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:13",
      "text": "Surely God will not hear vanity, neither will the Almighty regard it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.35.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:14",
      "text": "Although thou sayest thou shalt not see him, yet judgment is before him; therefore trust thou in him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.35.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:15",
      "text": "But now, because it is not so, he hath visited in his anger; yet he knoweth it not in great extremity:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.35.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:16",
      "text": "Therefore doth Job open his mouth in vain; he multiplieth words without knowledge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
